# BASELINE REPRODUCTION: Dotted Member Inference
# Validates that the analyzer successfully tracks dotted member access off of
# dynamically inferred objects or loop variables. When `alert.name` is referenced,
# the tool infers that it came from the `alerts` array that the loop iterates over.
# The tool MUST continue to support `_infer_member_source_for_token`.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: `dest` should be mapped to the `alerts` array with path `name`.
filter {
  for alert in alerts {
    mutate { replace => { "dest" => "%{alert.name}" } }
  }
}
